Charge decay time due to creation of point charges 
Let us now investigate the field instability of a pair of external
charges under the creation of two dynamical charges. Since point
charges have a singularity in the field energy at the core we
introduce again a cutoff  to regulate some of the infinities in
our calculations. First we will determine the energy gain due to the
presence of two point charges. We denote the two initial charges as
